content: Everything is ON. I have everything.
I have nothing. Wait, just a second. Uno momento por favor.
Oh, I started already. Phew! In my isolation?
Today is May 19th, 2022. It’s mission day 196. The time is 2:31PM. Three, two, one. //Mark!
Do you need a tissue? I’ll put it down there for you guys.
Why are you //lying, Ash? You are enjoying [UI]
We have to make them feel good.
Yeah, I might’ve been a little overboard there. Oh, shit!
Should I dilute it for you, Will?
It’s okay. It’s recorded, you know?
Vika, can you get me just some water?
Do you want it warm or cold?
I wish they gave us, like…
A survey, and there we would rate all the experiments. Which one we like and which one we don’t like.
Poop, sleep, and [SL] Belmont are going to be towards the bottom.
Yeah. Poop, sleep and [SL] Belmont. These three.
Too good, but I don’t know if there is any water there.
Average water loss…//not super, but not too bad.
//Why is my decision calculator is not showing?
This thing is not coming up for me. Decision calculator is //not showing up.
Log out and try to log in again.
//Why does it not want to work?
Sorry, I still can’t see it because I am having an issue.
Ask them. I still can’t check.
I assume there isn’t that much there.
It is very good for me. Did we find our point already?
Okay…This one is great – thirteen sixteen.
Yeah. …Not bad. //In fact, it is very…in fact, it is very good.
Because for me the loss is only 10%.
Well, I have 69% loss, but there is so much water there that it is not as important.
Please tell me what point it is.
The water is murky there, but it is well within the first step of cleaning. Only ten percent loss.
I understand that it is okay for Salya too. It’s not too deep.
Six twenty-nine. It’s not too bad either. I like all of them. Thirteen sixteen is the best in terms of the population, but…
I will tell you right now that it is good for Salya. You don’t need it. You will like it.
But twenty-eight twenty-one and thirteen sixteen were good in terms of water, correct?
So, I have water loss at 10% maximum.
Well, here’s another interesting one – twenty-three six.
Today, Oleg was active at first.
Today, for me it is for some reason…Usually, I mark points, and they are all…dirty water from which no…
Well, you have found water at 50% today. It is very good.
There, yes. But generally speaking, there is practically no clean water. So, we are having to…
Worse than those suggested by Oleg, but not too bad.
By way, for the most part, there is only hot water.
Why are you starting it? We were communicating just fine.
Ho ho ho, what about thirty-five two?
Is it your point or they sent you?
Such water in general…it is at the last one.
How could you? Shame! Shame! Shame!
There it is worse than in a puddle.
Between thirteen sixteen and twenty-five twenty-one which one do you like?
It was twenty-eight twenty-one. You said twenty-eight twenty-one, didn’t you?
It means that they will put in RIP.
Yes. “Large RIP” –  it means that you are not happy…It’s a slang expression for “you are wrong; you’ve made a huge mistake”.
And RIP – is it an acronym or is it a word?
Yes. “Rest in peace”. When people die, they count on it.
I like the subject today. //Rest quickly!
Are you and me in the same crew? Robotics?
It’s weird. I don’t think my chat is working, because I wrote in robotics and mine didn’t show up and I’m not getting those.
No, no. I wrote also in robotics.
Have the guys written to somebody?
Twenty-four forty-three. Ash has stopped here.
It’s just a thousand liters of water. In short, no water.
Operation specialist said: “Chicago vibes have arrived”.
Yuck! Let’s get rid of it. How could you?
Oh, that was the one…okay. I guess that’s the…They say eighteen one.
Did they look at any of the ones that we suggested yet?
Oh! Eighteen one is not too bad for me. Not bad at all.
A lot of water loss. //Оh! Why did they go so deep?
//Because for me it’s the best option.
According to the number of potential population reached. Over nine thousand. And the accessibility is quite high – 75%.
I did it again…Oh baby, baby.
Will, have you understood if there is any correlation with where there is a lot of water? Do you, besides the water basin itself, have some other parameter that would give you an idea?
What do you mean? So, it is…
Well, for me, for example, if it is deep, it may be clean. Surface water is dirtier. So, I can indirectly determine things by the water depth.
I have, specifically… specifically, the main formula is the average water loss. It depends on…

No. It depends on…there are two layers and there are two types of what the layers consist of. That is what determines the percentage of water loss. That’s all. But it doesn’t really affect it because either it’s already in the calculation, so I don’t have to do anything with it, but just say what percentage of water is lost and how much water there is there...
Sixteen six? Did anybody check sixteen six?
Shame. Why? They also //didn’t say anything about the points that we suggested.
The ones that Oleg suggested. Twenty-eight twenty-one and thirteen sixteen. They didn’t say anything.
We’ve checked eighteen one, right? It doesn’t work?
They said they are still holding on for eighteen one, hoping that it works, but you said 97% water loss there, right?
I mean, you end up with like …where is it? Like twelve thousand left. I mean, it’s not…
Liters left. And that’s just from after the loss. But then you have to filter it.
And does the temperature of the sand or soil affect things for someone?
Temperature. Is there such a parameter?
Perhaps, there is but…Yes, there is that one.
Yes, there is that here, but not…
What about twelve fourteen? Twelve fourteen?
What do you think of this one?
Do you want me to check that?
Did you get any response from them regarding the…
No. They seem to be ignoring us.
I mean, let’s let them. If they want to hunt, they’re gonna hunt. I mean…
Will, will. What do you think? //Twelve fourteen.
All in all, not too bad.
“Our team, generally, they didn’t like thirteen sixteen or twenty-eight twenty-one.”
Wow! One point away from mine.
Thirteen fourteen. Please check thirteen fourteen.
Ok. I will now work on the questions…
Oh, sorry. I had the survey questions so, I forgot.
It’s pretty good for me, actually. Yours too?
[SL] Okay, we will keep this one. Excellent.
Cool. And I have only just started…
What other points did we like?
It was like a mega one.
In my isolation? One more time?
Thirteen sixteen and thirteen fourteen – that one that you said…For me, all three of these points are with only minimal water loss.
Have they written anything to anybody? Is there any reaction?
Yes, one of my team is writing to me.
Only the meteorologist is writing to me.
Yeah, that’s the one that we took before.
Yeah, yeah. They didn’t like it.
No, // thirteen sixteen was the first point that we gave them.
Oh, I see, I see. Okay.
But thirteen fourteen, I hope they get back to us about.
Why your team is keeping silence?
Excuse me. The Martian terrain specialist is talking to me.
Don’t be hating on my team.
Congrats! They said: “Okay, that’s fine.” Thirteen fourteen.
[SL] We need to be finishing already.
Forty-six – forty-six, forty-three. It’s got a lot of water loss, but it’s got an awful lot available.
It’s bad for me. Bad, bad, bad.
Oh, wait, I am looking at my point. Oh, God. Look, who is such a Narcissus.
//Now bad. It’s too deep. I think it will be too expensive for Salik to extract this water.
Salah can pay for everything, right?
It’s okay, I am speaking for you.
Which point are you looking at, guys?
Forty-six forty-three. Who said this one?
Forty…they like forty-six forty-three. So, forty-six forty-three…
What happened to them liking thirteen fourteen?
Thirteen fourteen? Operation and drilling, they said it’s fine for them.
We agreed, yeah, with drilling and operation specialist. They said, that’s fine.
It’s still pretty bad compared to the others.
It’s pretty…it’s a lot of water.
Okay. I guess I can make it work.
Salya, it is good for you.
More than previous points. Thirteen fourteen…
Should I tell them it’s decent?
Is forty-six thirty-two good for everyone?
Forty-six thirty-two was okay for you? No?
Yes, here I can see it.
I put it in there. And then…
Now they are saying thirteen sixteen might be fine, but…
Was it from us or from them?
Yes, they have already agreed on that among themselves.
Alright. So, I don’t see them active.
I don’t see them active yet.
What indicator do you have? Is it nine thousand? Is it how much water there is at the depth?
Well, you have… oh, wait, it is wrong… Sedimentologist, here…temperature, temperature …Here, you have the indicator – it is…
Yeah, I do the last four. Somebody else on my team has to do the repair frequency. Later.
Actually, it looks like everything is filled in.
Salya, were you the first one to decide?
Are we going to sign? Yes?
Why is mine not showing? //I just did it.
[SL] Hydrologist okay. Operation, waiting for you.
Mine is still not showing up?
//Alright. Give them a second. Wait for Martian terrain specialist.
She already put her stuff in though.
They’ll click on it when they need to.
And who the freak changed my…!?
Who the heck is changing my…Martian terrain? You better not!!
Is someone changing it for you?
Changed //maintenance decision or changed usability decision?
//I’m changing it back. Hygiene, usability, maintenance, fund raising is on me. All those decisions are me. They are just repair frequency.
Come on, come on, maintenance specialist. Yeah! We are done, I think.
Interesting, do they fill questionnaires also?
I think they do. That and TTB.
Can we take a quick group photo at the end? Since we’re looking pretty?
Can we take a photo at the end? A group photo? Since the cameras are already there.
I see you are feeling bored. She is missing the letters. Read.
There’s a lot accumulated for you.
Oh, shit! Didn’t mean to do that.
Oh, I sent it to the wrong person.
Shoot! I sent it to the wrong place.
It was definitely yours. I know for sure.
